text.section:
A petitioner under this section shall attach to a petition:
all written consents for the guardianship that the petitioner has;
if applicable:
proof of guardianship or relinquishment of parental rights granted by an administrative, executive, or judicial body of a state or other jurisdiction; and
certification that the guardianship or relinquishment was granted in compliance with the jurisdiction's laws; and
a notice of filing that:
states the date on which the petition was filed;
identifies each person whose consent was filed with the petition;
states the obligation of a parent to give the juvenile court and local department notice of each change in the parent's address;
has printed on it the website that the Department maintains under § 2-302 of the Human Services Article; and
includes no identifying information that would be in violation of an agreement or consent.
